**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<item instructions>
/ 1 = "In this task you will try to memorize letters you see on the screen while you also read sentences.~n
In the next few minutes, you will have some practice to get you familiar with how the task works.~n
We will begin by practicing the letter part of the task.~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to begin."
/ 2 = "For this practice set, letters will appear on the screen one at a time.
Try to remember each letter in the order presented.~n
After 2-3 letters have been presented, you will see a screen listing 12 possible letters.
~n~n
Your job is to select each letter in the order presented.
To do this, <%expressions.buttoninstruct2%>.~n
The letters you select will appear at the bottom of the screen.~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to continue."
/ 3 = "When you have selected all the letters, and they are in the correct order, hit the EXIT box at the bottom right of the screen.~n
If you make a mistake, hit the CLEAR box to start over.~n
If you forget one of the letters, <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%> the BLANK box to mark the spot for the missing letter.~n
Remember, it is very important to get the letters in the same order as you saw them.
~nIf you forget one, use the BLANK box to mark the position.~n
Do you have any questions so far?~n~n~n
When you're ready, <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to start the letter practice."
/ 4 = "Now you will practice doing the sentence reading part of the task.~n~n
A sentence will appear on the screen, like this:~n
~"I like to run in the park.~"~n
As soon as you see the sentence, you should read it and determine if it makes sense or not. The above sentence makes sense.~n
An example of a sentence that does not make sense would be:~n
~"I like to run in the sky.~"~n
When you have read the sentence and determined whether it makes sense or not, <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%>.~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to continue."
/ 5 = "You will then see ~"This sentence makes sense.~" displayed on the next screen, along with a box marked TRUE and a box marked FALSE.~n
If the sentence on the previous screen made sense, <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%> on the TRUE box.
If the sentence did not make sense, <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%> the FALSE box.~n
After you <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%> one of the boxes, the computer will tell you if you made the right choice.~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to continue."
/ 6 = "It is VERY important that you answer the sentence problems correctly.
It is also important that you try and read the sentences as quickly as you can.~n
Do you have any questions?~n~n~n
When you're ready, <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to try some practice problems."
/ 7 = "Now you will practice doing both parts of the task at the same time.~n~n
In the next practice set, you will be given one sentence to read.
Once you make your decision about the sentence, a letter will appear on the screen. Try and remember the letter.~n
In the previous section where you only read the sentences, the computer computed your average time to read the sentences.~n
If you take longer than your average time, the computer will automatically move you onto the next letter part, thus skipping the True or False part and will count that problem as a sentence error.~n
Therefore it is VERY important to read the sentences as quickly and as accurately as possible.~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to continue."
/ 8 = "After the letter goes away, another sentence will appear, and then another letter.~n
At the end of each set of letters and sentences, a recall screen will appear.
<%expressions.buttoninstruct2%> to select the letters you just saw.
Try your best to get the letters in the correct order.~n
It is important to work QUICKLY and ACCURATELY on the sentences.
Make sure you know whether the sentence makes sense or not before moving on to the next screen.
You will not be told if your answer regarding the sentence is correct.~n
After the recall screen, you will be given feedback about your performance regarding both the number of letters recalled and the percent correct on the sentence problems.~n
Do you have any questions?~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to continue."
/ 9 = "During the feedback, you will see a number in red in the top right of the screen.
This indicates your percent correct for the sentence problems for the entire task.~n
It is VERY important for you to keep this at least at 85%.
For our purposes, we can only use data where the participant was at least 85% accurate on the sentences.~n
Therefore, in order for you to be asked to come back for future tasks, you must perform at least at 85% on the sentence problems WHILE doing your best to recall as many letters as possible.~n
Do you have any questions?~n~n~n
<%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to try some practice problems."
/ 10 = "That is the end of the practice.~n~n
The real trials will look like the practice trials you just completed.
First you will get a sentence to read, then a letter to remember.~n
When you see the recall screen, select the letters in the order presented.
If you forget a letter, <%expressions.buttoninstruct3%> the BLANK box to mark where it should go.~n
Some of the sets will have more sentences and letters than others.~n
It is important that you do your best on both the sentence problems and the letter recall parts of this task.~n
Remember for the sentences you must work as QUICKLY and ACCURATELY as possible. Also, remember to keep your sentence accuracy at 85% or above.~n
Do you have any questions?~n~n~n
If not, <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> to begin the task."
/ 11 = "Thank you for your participation."
</item>

****************************************************************************************************
general instruction expressions: adjust the instruction text depending on device used to run script
****************************************************************************************************
<expressions>
/ buttoninstruct1 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"tap the screen";} else {"click the mouse button";}
/ buttoninstruct2 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"tap the letters you want to select";} else {"use the mouse to select each letter";}
/ buttoninstruct3 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"tap";} else {"click";}
</expressions>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE LISTS: change editable lists here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

	The following list clements contain the set sizes used for the different study phases. 
	The set sizes determine how many letters the participant has to remember
	as well as the number of sentence problems she/he has to solve intermittently.	
	The task can be extended by modifying these values. The script can handle a maximum 
	set size of 12, task flow will be adjusted automatically.

**************************************************************************************************************
	Set Sizes for Letter Practice Phase
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: 2 repetitions of set sizes 2-3 for Letter only practice; order is sequential
<list PracLetterSetSize>
/ items = (2,2,3,3)
/ selectionmode = sequence
</list>

**************************************************************************************************************
	Set Sizes for Letter & Sentence Practice Phase
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: 3 repetitions of set size 2 for practice of Letter-Sentence Combos
<list PracBothSetSize>
/ items = (2,2,2)
/ selectionmode = sequence
</list>

**************************************************************************************************************
	Set Sizes for Letter & Sentence Test Phase
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: 3 repetitions of set sizes 3-7; order is randomly determined 
<list TestBothSetSize>
/ items = (3,3,3,4,4,4,5,5,5,6,6,6,7,7,7)
</list>


**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/ canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/ minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ screencolor = white
/ txcolor = black
/ txbgcolor = transparent
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 4.0%, true)
/ inputdevice = mouse
/ halign = center
/ valign = center
</defaults>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

********************
raw data
********************

<data>
/ columns = (build, computer.platform, date, time, subject, group, session, blockcode, blocknum, 
trialcode, trialnum, 
response, correct, latency, 
values.currentsetsize, text.letters.currentItem, values.sentenceproblemcount, values.sentencetimeout, 
text.PracSentenceProblem.currentItem, text.SentenceProblem.currentItem, values.sentenceaccuracy, 
values.sentencetotalerrors, values.sentenceaccerrors, values.sentencespeederrors, values.rspan,
values.recalledletters, values.totalcorrectletters, values.totalrecalledsets,

//trial data
values.trialCount,
values.recalledLetters_perTrial,
values.recalledLettersACC_perTrial,
values.correctSentences_perTrial,
values.sentenceACC_perTrial)
</data>

********************
summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, 
values.rspan, values.totalcorrectletters, values.sentencetotalerrors, values.sentencespeederrors, 
values.sentenceaccerrors)
</summarydata>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
 <values Arspan>
/ stopblock = 0
/ currentsetsize = 0
/ lettercount = 0
/ correctletters = 0
/ totalcorrectletters = 0
/ rspan = 0
/ totalrecalledsets = 0
/ recalledletters = ""
/ recallcount = 0
/ recalldelay = 0
/ sentenceaccuracy = 0
/ sentenceaccerrors = 0
/ sentencecurrenterrors = 0
/ sentencetotalerrors = 0
/ sentencespeederrors = 0
/ sentenceproblemcount = 0
/ sentenceerrorswitch = 1
/ sentencetimeout = 0

/trialCount = 0
/recalledLetters_perTrial = ""
/recalledLettersACC_perTrial = ""
/correctSentences_perTrial = ""
/sentenceACC_perTrial = ""
</values>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

	Letter String Generation is handled by two list elements:
	PracLetterlist and TestLetterlist.
	Letter Practice (Block PracLetter) uses sequential selection.
	Letter-Sentence Practice (Block PracBoth) and 
	Letter-Sentence Test (Block TestBoth) use random selection 
	without replacement for each sequence.
	Switching between lists according to current study phase
	is handled dynamically by 'expressions.selectionmode'.

<expressions Arspan>
/ selectionmode = if(script.currentblock=="PracLetter") PracLetterlist else TestLetterlist;
</expressions>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	INSTRUCTIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<block InstrPracLetter>
/ trials = [1-3=instructions]
/ recorddata = false
</block>

<block InstrPracSentence>
/ trials = [1-3=instructions]
/ recorddata = false
</block>

<block InstrPracBoth>
/ trials = [1-3=instructions]
/ recorddata = false
</block>

<block InstrTestBoth>
/ trials = [1=instructions]
/ recorddata = false
</block>

<block InstrFinal>
/ trials = [1 = score_report; 2=finish]
/ recorddata = false
</block>

<trial instructions>
/ pretrialpause = 250
/ posttrialpause = 250
/ stimulustimes = [1=instructions]
/ validresponse = (lbuttondown)
/ beginResponseTime = 2000
/ recorddata = false
</trial>

<text instructions>
/ items = instructions
/ hjustify = left
/ vjustify = center
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true)
/ size = (90%, 80%)
/ position = (50%, 50%)
/ select = sequence
/ resetinterval = 0
</text>

<trial finish>
/ stimulusFrames = [1 = clearScreen, finish]
/ timeout = 500
</trial>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	STIMULI
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<text LetterFeedback>
/ items = ("You recalled <%values.correctletters%> out of <%values.lettercount%> letters correctly.")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.5%, true)
/ position = (50%, 45%)
/ erase = true(white)
</text>

<text PracSentenceFeedback>
/ items = ("You were correct on <%trial.prac_solve_sentence.totalcorrectcount%> of <%list.PracSentencelist.itemCount%> trials.
That is <%trial.prac_solve_sentence.totalpercentcorrect%> percent correct.~n~n~n
Click the mouse button to continue.")
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, true)
/ size = (65%, 50%)
/ position = (50%, 50%)
/ vjustify = center
</text>

<text Letters>
/ items = letters_visual
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 5.0%, true)
/ erase = true(silver)
/ select = expressions.selectionmode
</text>


**************************************************************************************************************
	Empty Item Elements for Storing Presented and Recalled Letter Sequences
**************************************************************************************************************

<item PresentedLetters>
</item>

<item RecalledLetters>
</item>

